article.description: Devin Watson scored 18 points and San Francisco outscored Delaware State by 22 points in the second half to take a 67-47 victory on Sunday.
article.headline: Dons use big second half to overwhelm Delaware State 67-47
article.linkText: Dons use big second half to overwhelm Delaware State 67-47
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Devin Watson scored 18 points and San Francisco outscored Delaware State by 22 points in the second half to take a 67-47 victory on Sunday. The Hornets (0-7) made six 3-pointers and led 25-23 at halftime. But they shot just 28.6 percent in the second half when they made only 2 of 12 from the arc. The Dons (4-2) scored the first seven points of the second half. Runs of 16-0 and 12-0 expanded their lead to 27 points with 3:11 to go. Watson made four 3-pointers. Tim Derksen added 14 points. The Dons shot 61.5 percent in the second half. The Dons outrebounded the Hornets 41-31 and had a 30-10 advantage in the paint. DeAndre Haywood led the Hornets with 11 points, but they came all in the first half.
